President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. spoke with President Emmanuel Macron of France, Chancellor Olaf Scholz of Germany, Prime Minister Mario Draghi of Italy, and Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom to discuss their concerns about Russia's brutal tactics in Ukraine. They highlighted their ongoing support for Ukraine, including providing security assistance to Ukrainian defenders and humanitarian aid to those affected by the violence. The leaders also discussed recent diplomatic efforts to help Ukraine reach a ceasefire.